english:
  title: The Tower of Compassionate Protection Temple
  author: Heo Hong-jae
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Early I rise and climb the tower alone,
    Where autumn's eighth month stretches serene.
    White mist drifts across the distant fields,
    The crimson sun ascends the mountain's crest.
    On the traveler's path, wind and frost bite cold,
    Yet in the monk's quarters, flowers and trees rest in stillness.
    With a single cup we laugh and exchange words—
    All the world's hunger for fame and fortune fades away.
  footnotes:
    - The 'eighth month' of autumn refers to the traditional lunar calendar, suggesting late autumn in East Asian reckoning.
    - The contrast between the cold, exposed traveler's road and the serene, sheltered temple grounds reflects the poem's meditation on refuge and withdrawal from worldly concerns.
